Kolkata doctor found dead: Autopsy confirms sexual assault before murder, one held

timesofindia.com / Aug 10, 2024, 14:23 (IST)

Police arrested a suspect for the murder of a postgraduate trainee doctor at RG Kar Medical College in Kolkata. The woman's semi-nude body, showing signs of injury, was discovered in the seminar hall. Her father alleged rape and murder. The preliminary autopsy confirmed sexual abuse before death. Two intern doctors were also questioned in the ongoing investigation.

Udhyanidhi to become TN's deputy CM? Minister reveals

tnn / Aug 10, 2024, 13:02 (IST)

During an event in Ramanathapuram, Tamil Nadu minister R S Rajakannappan accidentally referred to Udhayanidhi Stalin as "deputy chief minister" before correcting himself to say he is the sports minister. The minister hinted Udhayanidhi could be called deputy CM after August 19. Speculation about Udhayanidhi's elevation gained traction despite official denials from DMK leadership.

tnn / Aug 09, 2024, 18:16 (IST)

As we begin the year-long centenary celebrations of the Kakori Train Action, TOI gives a lowdown on the event that gave a big push to the freedom struggle

Bengaluru techie couple loses Rs 1.53 crore in trading scam

timesofindia.com / Aug 10, 2024, 07:02 (IST)

A Bengaluru couple recovered Rs 1.4 crore out of the Rs 1.53 crore lost in an online trading scam, thanks to swift action by the East Division Cybercrime Police. The scammers, operating from the UK, had used mule accounts in North India to execute the fraud. Police investigation and coordination with banks were instrumental in recovering the funds.

'Bizmen behind bars because ...': Sisodia's big charge against BJP

timesofindia.com / Aug 10, 2024, 14:41 (IST)

Following his release from jail, AAP leader Manish Sisodia criticized the Modi government and BJP for allegedly targeting opposition members through central agencies. He termed Arvind Kejriwal, who remains in jail, as a symbol of honesty. Sisodia praised the Supreme Court's verdict and urged party workers to fight against what he called dictatorship.
